feat(us3): land narrator dialog minimal slice + restart-hang fix

Closes T047–T050 of the 001 vertical slice; T051 playtest sign-off
checklist authored and pending maintainer walk-through.

What landed:

- src/data/narrator-beats.ts (T047): one after-spawn beat for level-01
  with original prose per Constitution Principle I / spec FR-029.
- src/systems/narrator-trigger.ts (T048): pure evaluator covering all
  three NarratorTrigger kinds (after-spawn, on-position, on-event).
- tests/unit/narrator-beats.test.ts: 3 tests for the evaluator,
  asserting each kind's firing condition independently.
- src/scenes/LevelScene.ts: per-frame beat evaluation, single active
  beat at a time, registry-driven dismiss handshake, init() resets
  fired-beat state so replays re-fire (T050).
- src/scenes/UIScene.ts (T049): bottom-center dialog box with cream
  border, body text, Space/Enter keyboard dismiss + tap/click
  dismiss. Lazy-built on first beat; reused on subsequent beats.
- src/scenes/BootScene.ts: defensive transition when the loader queue
  ends up empty on restart (every asset already cached). Without
  this, Play-again stuck on "Loading…" because Phaser's COMPLETE
  event does not fire reliably with an empty queue across versions.

Spec coverage:

- US3 AS-1: dialog appears ~2s after spawn with original tutorial prose.
- US3 AS-2: assigned dismiss inputs (Space / Enter / tap / click)
  remove the dialog and play continues.
- US3 AS-3: dialog never blocks input; dismiss affordance always
  visible.
- US3 AS-4: replay re-fires the beat at the same trigger.

Architecture notes:

- Narrator data composition happens in LevelScene rather than the
  pure level-loader so the loader stays Tiled-format-focused and
  the beat list can later vary per save/profile without changing
  the .tmj contract.
- The dismiss handshake uses the scene registry (REGISTRY_KEY_
  NARRATOR_TEXT). LevelScene publishes the beat text; UIScene
  clears the key on dismiss; LevelScene's CHANGE_DATA_KEY watcher
  drops `activeBeatId` so the next eligible beat can fire. This
  keeps UI and gameplay decoupled (Principle XI / IV).

Gates: typecheck / lint / 99 tests / build all green.

Playtest checklist: specs/001-vertical-slice/playtests/us3.md.
HANDOVER.md updated to reflect US3 minimal feature-complete state.
feat(us2-full): powerup + SaveService persistence

Closes US2 feature work. Walking into the gold powerup makes the
hero immune for ~5 seconds (visible gold tint + top-center HUD
timer counting down); slime contact during that window passes
through without taking damage. Level-complete writes the run's
progress to localStorage (carrots collected + level marked done);
the data survives browser restarts. Final step before US2 ships:
maintainer plays through the new playtest sections + signs off.

What's in this commit
=====================

Pure-logic foundation
- src/entities/hero-powerup.ts: HeroPowerupState — pure timer with
  three configurable stack modes (refresh / extend / ignore) for
  what happens when re-granted while already powered. Production
  uses "refresh" (POWERUPS.invincibilityStackMode); the other two
  are documented + tested for the polish phase.
- tests/unit/hero-powerup.test.ts: 9 cases covering initial state,
  fresh grant, all three stack modes both while powered and after
  expiry.

Hero powerup integration
- src/entities/hero.ts: imports + instantiates HeroPowerupState.
  takeHit() short-circuits with "ignored" when powered.
  Visual feedback split: powered → gold tint
  (matches PALETTE.uiPowerup); invuln post-hit → alpha-cycle blink;
  neither → normal sprite. Three new public methods:
  applyPowerup(durationMs), isPowered(), getPowerupRemainingMs().

Pickup powerup branch
- src/entities/pickup.ts: removed the earlier `throw` on powerup
  config. Both kinds (carrot / powerup) now share the same static-
  body construction; difference is just the frame index (heart-
  shaped tile, frame 44 — eyeballed) and a gold tint that distinguishes
  the powerup visually from the orange carrot at a glance.

LevelScene wiring
- Powerup overlap → hero.applyPowerup(entity.durationMs) + initial
  publish of remaining ms to the registry.
- Per-frame update() publishes hero.getPowerupRemainingMs()
  rounded to 100ms (so registry CHANGE_DATA_KEY doesn't fire 60×/sec).
  Phaser's registry.set fires the change event on every call
  regardless of value change, so the rounding-guard is the
  caller's responsibility.
- New REGISTRY_KEY_POWERUP_REMAINING_MS export.
- Seeds the registry key to 0 in init() so the HUD has a clean
  starting state.

SaveService integration
- src/game.ts: postBoot now constructs LocalStorageSaveService and
  mounts it on the registry under REGISTRY_KEY_SAVE_SERVICE. The
  construction is wrapped in try/catch — if window.localStorage is
  disabled (incognito + storage-disabled corner cases) we log + continue;
  the game still plays, just session-only.
- LevelScene.endLevel("complete") → persistProgress() reads current
  SaveState, appends this levelId to completedLevelIds, adds this
  run's carrotsCollected to lifetimeCarrots, writes. Failure is
  non-blocking (logged + ignored) per the design rule.
- "gameover" outcome does NOT persist anything; you lost.

UIScene HUD power-up timer
- New powerTimerText field. Top-center of the HUD, gold text on
  dialog-dark background. Visible only when remaining > 0;
  auto-hides on expiry. Subscribes to
  REGISTRY_KEY_POWERUP_REMAINING_MS via the standard registry
  CHANGE_DATA_KEY listener.

Level data
- src/data/levels/level-01.tmj: one powerup ("shield-1") added at
  (612, 288), floor height between platform 3 and the slime patrol
  area. Maintainer can walk through, grab it, immediately run into
  slime to verify invincibility.

T046 playtest checklist
- specs/001-vertical-slice/playtests/us2.md: replaced the "deferred"
  block with the actual powerup + cross-session persistence sections.
  Persistence section explicitly mentions dev-tools verification of
  the localStorage key + the private/incognito non-crash expectation.

HANDOVER + journal
- HANDOVER bumped from "US2 alpha" to "US2 feature-complete pending
  sign-off". Tree + next-actions refreshed.
- Journal entry 2026-05-19-us2-full-powerup-saveservice.md
  documents the powerup integration, the registry-spam discovery
  (and the rounding-guard fix), the test-first pattern continuing
  to pay off.

Repo-memory updates
- Added the "Phaser registry.set fires CHANGE_DATA_KEY on every
  call" gotcha so the rounding-guard pattern is recorded for next
  time.

