feat(us1): T035 mobile touch controls + GameOverScene Enter-restart fix

US1 is now feature-complete on both desktop AND mobile. The vertical
slice plays end-to-end on a phone with three on-screen buttons (◄ ►
JUMP); desktop is unchanged. A small bug-fix for the Game Over
keyboard-restart is bundled in.

Two final steps before US1 is officially shipped:
  1. Maintainer walks the playtest checklist on a phone.
  2. Sign-off line at the bottom of specs/001-vertical-slice/playtests/us1.md.
Then US2 (T041, first enemy) begins.

What's in this commit
=====================

T035 — Mobile touch controls
- src/systems/touch-input-store.ts: singleton store with boolean flags
  (left/right held) + edge-detected jump-press (consumeJumpPressed()
  mirrors Phaser.Input.Keyboard.JustDown() semantics). Pure logic, no
  Phaser, no DOM.
- tests/unit/touch-input-store.test.ts: 10 cases including the
  edge-detect contract (setJump(true) twice in a row fires one press;
  release-then-press fires a new press).
- src/scenes/UIScene.ts: full rewrite from stub. Feature-detects touch
  via `'ontouchstart' in window || navigator.maxTouchPoints > 0`. On
  touch devices, builds three 88×88 px translucent buttons at the
  bottom of the screen (◄ ► on the left for thumb-rolling, JUMP on
  the right). Buttons stay screen-fixed via setScrollFactor(0).
  Pointer events (pointerdown / pointerup / pointerupoutside /
  pointerout) write to TouchInputStore; the "outside" event handles
  finger-slides-off-button-while-pressed (otherwise the button stays
  stuck in the pressed state).
- Portrait-orientation prompt: matchMedia("(orientation: portrait)")
  with a change listener (modern + legacy addListener fallback).
  Translucent full-canvas overlay with the localized rotate text;
  auto-dismisses on landscape rotation. No screen.orientation.lock()
  call — iOS Safari rejects, Chrome requires fullscreen; the visual
  prompt is the cross-browser fallback. PWA manifest still declares
  landscape so installed PWAs lock natively.
- src/entities/hero.ts: per-frame input snapshot now OR-merges touch
  flags with keyboard flags via nullish-coalesced reads. Hero's
  resolver doesn't change — same HeroInput shape, additional source.
- src/scenes/LevelScene.ts: launches UIScene in create() (parallel
  scene, gameplay continues underneath) and stops it on end-trigger
  so touch buttons / portrait overlay don't sit on top of
  GameOverScene.
- src/game.ts: postBoot now seeds TouchInputStore on the registry
  alongside AssetService (Principle XI: services live on the registry,
  not on globals).
- src/config/ui.ts: new touch* constants — button size, three position
  offsets, opacity (idle + pressed), label font size. Tuning these is
  a code-no-change tuning iteration.
- src/i18n/en.ts: new keys for ◄ / ► / JUMP labels + the rotate prompt.
  Glyphs in t() to keep the translation seam complete.

Bug fix — GameOverScene Enter / Space restart
- src/scenes/GameOverScene.ts: replaced
  `keydown-${Phaser.Input.Keyboard.KeyCodes.ENTER.toString()}` with
  `"keydown-ENTER"`. Phaser keyboard event names use the KEY NAME, not
  the numeric KeyCode (.toString() produced "keydown-13" which Phaser
  never fires). Same fix for SPACE. Added a comment explaining the
  gotcha so this doesn't recur. Recorded as a transferable Phaser
  gotcha in repo memory.

T037 playtest checklist — mobile section enabled
- specs/001-vertical-slice/playtests/us1.md: replaced the "DEFERRED to
  T035" note with the actual mobile checklist (button visibility on
  phone vs desktop, hold + release behavior, slide-off-while-pressed,
  no accidental gameplay-area taps, portrait prompt visibility, camera
  follow on phone, end-trigger + game-over flow via touch).

HANDOVER.md
- Current-task line, TL;DR (US1 feature-complete pending sign-off),
  on-disk tree (touch-input-store + UIScene with real description),
  what's-NOT-on-disk (removed T035 row; HUD + entities + hero-death
  remain), next-3-actions (playtest → sign off → start T041).

