feat(us1): T033 + T034 finish + T036 + T037 — US1 desktop-playable

US1 (P1 MVP-floor) is now playable end-to-end on desktop. The hero
walks, jumps (with coyote + buffer + variable-height), lands on the
three Tiled-authored platforms, reaches the orange end-trigger, sees
"Level complete!", and can restart with one click. Only T035 (mobile
touch + landscape lock) remains before US1 fully ships on both
desktop and mobile.

What's in this commit
=====================

T033 — Hero entity (with a pure-logic split for testability)
- src/entities/hero-input.ts: pure decision function
  resolveHeroFrameAction({ input, coyote, buffer, nowMs, isOnGround,
  upwardVelocityPxPerSec }) → { moveDirection, jumpFired,
  applyJumpReleaseCap }. Zero Phaser imports. The whole jump-feel
  contract (variable-height release-cap, coyote-time, jump-buffer,
  both-held-direction-cancel) lives here, free of WebGL.
- src/entities/hero.ts: Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite wrapper. Owns
  CoyoteTimer + JumpBuffer + keyboard handlers (←→A D + ↑W Space).
  Per-frame update() builds the input snapshot, runs the resolver,
  applies the resulting action to the Arcade body. Re-exports the
  hero-input types so callers have one import path.
- tests/unit/hero.test.ts: 13 cases covering every branch of the
  resolver. All RED until the resolver existed, then GREEN on first
  implementation — no debug iteration. Split exists specifically so
  the tests don't pull in Phaser (which needs a window to load).

T034 — LevelScene finished
- Refactored create() into seven private methods (read cache, parse,
  build tilemap, render with collision, spawn hero, configure camera,
  set up end-trigger) so each step is one named concept.
- Terrain layer now setCollisionByExclusion([-1, 0]) — every non-zero
  tile id is solid. Granular per-tile collision (one-way platforms,
  etc.) can be added later by toggling specific ids without changing
  this default.
- Hero spawned at level.spawn.{x,y}; physics.add.collider(hero,
  terrain) wires the floor.
- Camera switched from centerOn(spawn) to startFollow(hero, true) —
  the `true` second arg = roundPixels to avoid sub-pixel jitter on
  tile edges during scroll.
- End-trigger overlap: an invisible add.zone matching
  level.endTrigger.{x,y,w,h} fires `scene.start("GameOverScene",
  { outcome: "complete", levelId })` on overlap, after pausing this
  scene to avoid the overlap re-firing in the next few frames.
- Subtle orange outlined rectangle visualizes the end-trigger so the
  player can see where to head. Uses PALETTE_HEX.uiCarrot per
  Principle III.
- Phaser 4 type-narrowing fix: map.createLayer() now returns
  TilemapLayer | TilemapGPULayer; narrowed via instanceof before
  assigning to the classic-only typed variable.

T036 — GameOverScene full rewrite
- Two outcomes via init(data): "complete" → t("outcome.levelComplete"),
  "gameover" → t("outcome.gameOver"). The "gameover" path is declared
  but not yet fired (no hero-death until US2 enemies).
- Dimmed panel + headline + large carrot-orange Play-again button.
  Mouse hover lifts the color to cream; mouse click, Enter, and Space
  all trigger restart.
- Restart goes BootScene → fresh LevelScene cycle (cleanest reset
  given the LevelScene was paused on the end-trigger overlap).

T037 — Manual playtest checklist
- specs/001-vertical-slice/playtests/us1.md: full per-build checklist
  covering setup, keyboard play-through (movement, jump, variable-
  height, coyote, buffer, no-double-jump, platform sequence, world
  bounds), end-trigger + game-over flow, mobile section deferred to
  T035, spec acceptance cross-reference, tuning-observations block,
  sign-off line. Required by Constitution Principle VI (gameplay-feel
  rule): code can be unit-tested; how the game feels cannot.

HANDOVER.md
- TL;DR + on-disk tree + what's-NOT + next-3-actions all refreshed for
  the new state. T035 + T037 sign-off are the two open items before
  US1 is fully shipped.

