T031 — Asset declarations
- src/services/asset-service.ts: replaced the loose AssetDeclaration
  interface with a discriminated union (ImageAssetDeclaration |
  SpritesheetAssetDeclaration). Image variant carries an optional
  `tilesetName` field — the seam by which LevelScene binds a .tmj's
  tileset to its loaded image at scene build time, supporting
  multi-tileset levels natively. KennyAssetService.assets now has
  two real entries: the tileset image (tilesetName matches the .tmj)
  and the character spritesheet (frame 0 = hero placeholder).

T032 — BootScene real implementation
- src/scenes/BootScene.ts: full rewrite from stub. Resolves the
  requested level's URL via LevelRegistry (async dynamic import),
  queues the tilemap JSON + every AssetService declaration on the
  Phaser loader, transitions to LevelScene when the loader fires
  COMPLETE. Shows a brief "Loading…" message during preload. Owns
  the FPS overlay (until UIScene graduates at T035). Exports
  REGISTRY_KEY_ASSET_SERVICE so other scenes can retrieve the
  shared service without a string-key drift risk.

